The Sistine Chapel will be closed to the public from Monday 28 April "for the needs of the Conclave". The Holy See makes it known. "All visits to the Vatican Gardens and the Necropolis of the Via Triumphalis are also suspended." The Direction of Museums and Cultural Heritage, "in expressing deep mourning and pain for the disappearance of the Holy Father", we read, that Saturday, 26 April, "the Vatican Museums and the Museums of Castel Gandolfo will be closed to the public, as a sign of mourning, for the funerals of the Roman Pontiff Francis".
<h2> S.Lorenzo's fans, "best player world"</h2>
A Mass for Pope Francis >, the most famous fan of the team and "best player of the world >". Almost two hundred supporters of the Argentine team of San Lorenzo de Almagro> participated in the religious function, held at the Chapel of San Antonio in the district of Almagro in Buenos Aires, where Salesian priest Lorenzo Massa founded the club "azulgrana" in 1908 to tear the boys to the street.<br> "Fin as a child, Father Jorge (Bergoglio) was passionate about the teachings of Father Lorenzo. Father Lorenzo knew how to take care of those who did not see, and Francis, imitating Father Lorenzo, knew how to take care of those who did not notice", said Father Juan Pablo Sclippa, who offered the Mass. In his homily, Sclippa underlined that the Pope "was a great man who knew how to be small, a truly great man, the best player in the field, yet he never believed".
<div </div
"For the club, the Pope meant something very important because, besides being the Pope of the whole world, he was the Pope of San Lorenzo. He grew up here and brought the colors of San Lorenzo to the heart," said Miguel ngel Delgado, 77 years old, a fan of "El Ciclo'n" present at Mass, convinced that "from up there" the Pope "will help" the team he loved.
Bergoglio, a descendant of Italian immigrants born in Buenos Aires in 1936, inherited the passion for San Lorenzo from his father. The colors of the club are the same as the mantle of the Virgin Mary Helper, a Marian devotion dear to the pontiff and whose image is also venerated in the Chapel of St. Anthony. During the Mass, a flag with the colors of the club and the face of Pope Francis was arranged in front of the altar of the chapel.&nbsp;
